  1	# Spirit judge cutover and rollback
  2	
  3	## Purpose
  4	
  5	This runbook changes the fail-closed Spirit judge path without exposing prompts,
  6	records, diagnostics, or credential material. `signal-spirit-judge` is the typed
  7	wire contract, `spirit-judge` is the socket executable, `judge` owns provider
  8	mechanics, and `spirit-judge-config` is public declarative prompt and catalogue
  9	data.
 10	
 11	## Pin and build order
 12	
 13	1. Land and push contract/provider producers.
 14	2. Land and push `spirit-judge`; verify its Cargo lock pins the provider commit.
 15	3. Land and push `spirit-judge-config` policy/documentation.
 16	4. Update and validate the `CriomOS-home` lock, where the actual Nix service
 17	   arguments select provider, model, effort, timeout, and authorization mode.
 18	5. Update and validate this deployment flake lock to the exact Home commit.
 19	6. Deploy only the pushed immutable deployment revision through Lojix.
 20	
 21	The catalogue policy file is declarative. The Home service command is the
 22	operative selection source and must be inspected or tested for the exact
 23	`openai-codex`, model, effort, timeout, and external-session reference.
 24	
 25	## Source-ready pin preflight
 26	
 27	Before live cutover, machine-check the deployment lock chain is exactly:
 28	
 29	- `signal-spirit-judge` `8f24ff2198a861eeb13ac54087447cf651de18b3`;
 30	- `spirit-judge` `33ca69b6c5d9e781f38ba3d62467606f98f45894`;
 31	- `spirit-judge-config` `b6a3fe7e0f91f2e5ff8ddec94ebfe2b489fc355d`;
 32	- `spirit` `28a909bc7d89a8165d42e1c4ea906cc055edd962`; and
 33	- `CriomOS-home` `9427e25aedd544021da2d9d8373f069ff1005fa6`.
 34	
 35	The Home fake deployment check proves only rendered service wiring and argv.
 36	The separate `spirit-judge-cli-contract` check invokes the real package's
 37	unauthenticated usage boundary; neither check authenticates or calls a model.
 38	
 39	## Authorization and provider witnesses
 40	
 41	`codex-login` means the configured Codex executable's pre-existing ambient
 42	session. It is not a bearer secret and does not select an account. Before
 43	activation, obtain authority that the ambient session is the intended account
 44	through an approved non-secret status interface. If that cannot be bounded, keep
 45	both `spirit-judge` and its dependent `spirit-daemon` stopped.
 46	
 47	For Luna compatibility and Terra production witnesses, record only:
 48	
 49	- timestamp;
 50	- executable revision;
 51	- model and effort;
 52	- exit status; and
 53	- parsed verdict class.
 54	
 55	Do not retain prompts, record text, provider output, diagnostics, account data,
 56	or credentials. Run fake-executable tests for argv/auth/timeout mechanics and
 57	use at most one approved authenticated call for each live model witness.
 58	
 59	## Database safety
 60	
 61	Before deployment, create a byte-preserving private backup of the production
 62	store and verify it without reading records. On the live store, use only a
 63	marker query. A stable `(commit-sequence state-digest)` marker is evidence that
 64	the committed record and referent corpus is unchanged even when database pages
 65	are rewritten after restart. Keep the backup through acceptance. Accepted-write
 66	checks belong only to a private exact copy or a supported reversible namespace.
 67	
 68	## Activation and fail-closed checks
 69	
 70	Deploy with `ActivateNow` using the immutable deployment revision, then confirm
 71	Lojix reports a new `Current` generation. Verify both services are active and
 72	the live judge process argv has the pinned executable plus the exact provider,
 73	model, effort, timeout, and external-session reference. Restart the judge and
 74	confirm its dependent Spirit service returns active; unavailable, malformed,
 75	timeout, and provider failures must remain typed rejections before any write.
 76	
 77	## Rollback
 78	
 79	If the judge cannot authenticate, start, or satisfy the fail-closed checks, stop
 80	`spirit-judge.service`; its required Spirit dependency must not provide a write
 81	path. Re-activate the prior known-good immutable CriomOS deployment revision
 82	through Lojix, wait for it to become `Current`, and verify the previous service
 83	argv and marker. Do not restore the production database merely because its bytes
 84	differ after a restart; restore only from the preserved backup under explicit
 85	recovery authority and after comparing the logical marker.
  1	{
  2	  config,
  3	  inputs,
  4	  lib,
  5	  pkgs,
  6	  horizon,
  7	  user,
  8	  ...
  9	}:
 10	let
 11	  inherit (lib)
 12	    mkIf
 13	    mkOption
 14	    ;
 15	  inherit (lib.types) bool;
 16	  inherit (user) size;
 17	
 18	  system = pkgs.stdenv.hostPlatform.system;
 19	  agentPackage = inputs.agent.packages.${system}.default;
 20	  spiritPackage = inputs.spirit.packages.${system}.default;
 21	  spiritJudgePackage = inputs.spirit-judge.packages.${system}.default;
 22	  spiritJudgeConfig = inputs.spirit-judge-config;
 23	  codexCliPackage = inputs.codex-cli.packages.${system}.default;
 24	
 25	  # These values configure the retained agent daemon only. Spirit judgment is
 26	  # served by the separate OpenAI Codex adapter below.
 27	  providerName = "deepseek";
 28	  defaultModel = "deepseek-v4-flash";
 29	  providerEndpoint = "https://api.deepseek.com/v1";
 30	  providerGopassPath = "platform.deepseek.com/api-key";
 31	
 32	  # The agent daemon resolves its own provider credential at runtime. No secret
 33	  # value is embedded in this Nix configuration.
 34	  agentServicePath = lib.concatStringsSep ":" [
 35	    "${config.home.homeDirectory}/.nix-profile/bin"
 36	    "/run/current-system/sw/bin"
 37	    "/run/wrappers/bin"
 38	  ];
 39	
 40	  stateDirectory = "${config.home.homeDirectory}/.local/state/spirit";
 41	  socketPath = "${stateDirectory}/spirit.sock";
 42	  metaSocketPath = "${stateDirectory}/meta-spirit.sock";
 43	  spiritJudgeSocketPath = "${stateDirectory}/spirit-judge.sock";
 44	  databasePath = "${stateDirectory}/spirit.sema";
 45	  configurationPath = "spirit.config.rkyv";
 46	
 47	  agentStateDirectory = "${config.home.homeDirectory}/.local/state/agent";
 48	  agentSocketPath = "${agentStateDirectory}/agent.sock";
 49	  agentMetaSocketPath = "${agentStateDirectory}/agent-meta.sock";
 50	  agentDatabasePath = "${agentStateDirectory}/agent.sema";
 51	  agentConfigurationPath = "agent.config.rkyv";
 52	
 53	  agentDaemonConfiguration = pkgs.runCommand "agent-daemon-configuration" { } ''
 54	    set -eu
 55	
 56	    mkdir -p "$out"
 57	    ${agentPackage}/bin/agent-write-configuration \
 58	      "(AgentConfigurationWriteRequest (${agentSocketPath} ${agentMetaSocketPath} 384 ${agentDatabasePath} [(ProviderSeed (${providerName} ${providerEndpoint} ${defaultModel} (Gopass ${providerGopassPath})))] $out/${agentConfigurationPath}))" \
 59	      > "$out/configuration-written.nota"
 60	    test -s "$out/${agentConfigurationPath}"
 61	  '';
 62	
 63	  # The compatibility-named configuration field now carries only Spirit's
 64	  # typed judge socket and timeout. Provider/model selection belongs to the
 65	  # adapter service, not the Spirit daemon, so the legacy provider fields stay
 66	  # empty and cannot silently select a fallback judge.
 67	  guardianAgentConfiguration = "(Some (${spiritJudgeSocketPath} None None 180000 None))";
 68	
 69	  # AuthorizationMode gates the separate criome/mirror path. `Gating` remains
 70	  # Spirit's default; judge admission is independently mandatory through the
 71	  # configured typed judge socket.
 72	  authorizationMode = "Gating";
 73	
 74	  daemonConfiguration = pkgs.runCommand "spirit-daemon-configuration" { } ''
 75	    set -eu
 76	
 77	    mkdir -p "$out"
 78	    ${spiritPackage}/bin/spirit-write-configuration \
 79	      "(ConfigurationWriteRequest (${socketPath} (Some ${metaSocketPath}) ${databasePath} None ${authorizationMode} ${guardianAgentConfiguration} $out/${configurationPath}))" \
 80	      > "$out/configuration-written.nota"
 81	    test -s "$out/${configurationPath}"
 82	  '';
 83	
 84	  migrateState = ''
 85	    ${spiritPackage}/bin/spirit-migrate-store \
 86	      "($database_path)"
 87	  '';
 88	
 89	  activateState = pkgs.writeShellScript "spirit-activation-state" ''
 90	    set -eu
 91	
 92	    state_directory=${lib.escapeShellArg stateDirectory}
 93	    agent_state_directory=${lib.escapeShellArg agentStateDirectory}
 94	
 95	    ${pkgs.coreutils}/bin/mkdir -p "$state_directory"
 96	    ${pkgs.coreutils}/bin/mkdir -p "$agent_state_directory"
 97	  '';
 98	
 99	  initializeAgentState = pkgs.writeShellScript "agent-startup-state" ''
100	    set -eu
101	
102	    agent_state_directory=${lib.escapeShellArg agentStateDirectory}
103	
104	    ${pkgs.coreutils}/bin/mkdir -p "$agent_state_directory"
105	    ${pkgs.coreutils}/bin/rm -f \
106	      ${lib.escapeShellArg agentSocketPath} \
107	      ${lib.escapeShellArg agentMetaSocketPath}
108	  '';
109	
110	  initializeState = pkgs.writeShellScript "spirit-startup-state" ''
111	    set -eu
112	
113	    state_directory=${lib.escapeShellArg stateDirectory}
114	    database_path=${lib.escapeShellArg databasePath}
115	
116	    ${pkgs.coreutils}/bin/mkdir -p "$state_directory"
117	    ${pkgs.coreutils}/bin/rm -f \
118	      ${lib.escapeShellArg socketPath} \
119	      ${lib.escapeShellArg metaSocketPath}
120	
121	    ${migrateState}
122	  '';
123	
124	  initializeJudgeState = pkgs.writeShellScript "spirit-judge-startup-state" ''
125	    set -eu
126	
127	    ${pkgs.coreutils}/bin/mkdir -p ${lib.escapeShellArg stateDirectory}
